# ========================================
# NOTES
# ========================================

# 1. Copy this file to .env.local for local development
# 2. Add .env.local to .gitignore (NEVER commit secrets!)
# 3. For production, set these in your hosting platform:
#    - Vercel: Project Settings → Environment Variables
#    - Netlify: Site Settings → Build & Deploy → Environment
#    - AWS: Parameter Store or Secrets Manager
# 4. Use NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix for client-side variables only
# 5. Keep server-side secrets without NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix
# 6. Generate strong secrets: openssl rand -base64 32
